About
If you’ve always wanted to be a spy, head over to SPYSCAPE, an attraction dedicated entirely to espionage. Here, you can complete timed coding puzzles at the Encryption Gallery, take a lie detector test at the Deception Gallery, navigate a tangle of lasers at the Special Ops Gallery, check out the special 007 exhibit, and read about the stories of real spies through the ages. Visit during exciting events like Story Mondays, or the Spyflix and Spycon Festivals. The attraction is free with the New York Sightseeing Pass. The Go City: New York Explorer Pass also give you discounted admission. – Tripadvisor
Duration: 1-2 hours

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Midtown
This is the iconic New York that so many visitors imagine before they visit - spectacular skyscrapers like the Chrysler Building and Empire State Building, iconic public buildings like Grand Central Terminal and the New York Public Library, and the non-stop hustle and bustle of the city streets. Fifth Avenue is a shopper's paradise where you can find every kind of store imaginable, with fashion brands ranging from the affordable to the ultra-fancy. Visit Rockefeller Center to experience towering Art Deco grandeur, and foodies will love the busy restaurants that stay open late in Koreatown. After dark, Midtown calms down a bit, but at any time of day or night it still feels 100% New York.

The recount of the experience and my review: So, I would go back but... I had just given it a 10/10 at the location survey and then I played one more game, the room #1 and got hurt trying to collect points for my team. The issue with that game is that in the middle of it by round 2 or 3, one of the circles where you have to jump to, moves too close to the exit door and there's an edge that needs to be boldened more and also the circle needs to move further from it, so people do not hit that edge by trying to just enjoy the game and get points. I told this to the location staff, so I am writing this review just in case so this gets taken care of to prevent someone else from getting hurt (specially to prevent a child from getting hurt) and so that therefore Spyscape keeps operating because besides that we had fun, and it is a very interesting spot. I would go back, but I would suggest that the issue gets fixed on game room #1 and for them to check other games too for safety just in case. (see photos I submitted). Thank you for reading. Interesting but Overpriced
Jul 2024 • Family
I visited Spyscape with my son while on vacation in NYC. We opted to complete the Discover your Spy Role section, so this review is only related to that option and not the Spy Games section.

While there were many espionage articles and information throughout the course of the section we were in, there was really very limited interactive tasks to complete which was primarily the reason we chose that experience. With such limited interactive tasks, it's really hard to feel like their spy role assessment had any merit. If you chose this option, it is best for visitors that are interested in seeing a variety of exhibits and stories related to former spy activity. If that is not your game, then this would be a pass. Again, not sure of the gaming side of the experiences.
